  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you're looking for easy access to the slopes, Sporthotel Panorama's the place for you. It’s got a piste-side location 1,700 metres above <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Corvara</a>, so grabbing your skis and getting down the mountain couldn’t be easier. The centre of Covara is around fifteen minutes walk away, or you can make the most of the shuttle service.</p>
<h2>Slope access</h2>
<p>Set above the resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Covara</a>, the Sporthotel has wonderful views of the surrounding mountain peaks and even better access to the slopes. The Arlaral lift is a snowballs throw away giving you access for cruisy blues and reds - perfect for the first run of the day. When its time to return home, there is no need to rush back as you can ski straight back to the door. The centre of Covara is a fifteen minute walk away or you can hop on the shuttle bus.</p>
<h2>Alpine style</h2>
<p>The Costamoling family and their team loving run the Sporthotel, offering typical Tyrolean hospitality with a smile. Furnished in a traditional Alpine style, the hotel provides a cosy retreat in Covara. The spacious rooms are traditional with lot's of pine furniture and wood panelling, each equipped with all of the modern conveniences needed for a comfortable stay in the <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites</a>. Most of the rooms are located in the main building, however there are also some in the adjacent building across the road, connected by an underground passageway.</p>
<p>The meals are hearty and filling. Fuel up for a day on the Sellaronda at the extensive breakfast buffet, and when you return enjoy a delicious four course evening meal. The menu often includes a mix of local and international dishes, featuring natural ingredients which showcase the best of the region’s cuisine. The hotel also has an <span>à la carte restaurant, Stüa Ladina, serving a variety of different dishes in a cosy Alpine style restaurant (pay locally). </span>Don’t forget to order a bottle of local wine to go with your meal.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa</h2>
<p>There is nowhere better to unwind than in the hotels wellness area. Have a dip in the panoramic indoor pool before heading to the spa area with a variety of different saunas. Choose between the <span>Finnish sauna, crystal sauna, hayshed sauna, or the infrared sauna - there is also a Turkish steam bath, Kneipp and immersion pool. If</span> you fancy a bit of pampering, book in for a massage – it'll refresh you before another day of skiing.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Sporthotel Panorama the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
